Postprocessing class

This document demonstrates the functions in the Postprocessing() class. The class methods can be viewed in src/postprocessing.R.

First set the start and end dates to extract from the example database.

# Set the start and end date to postprocess
start_dt <- as_datetime('2021-09-01T00:00:00', tz='UTC')
end_dt   <- as_datetime('2021-10-01T00:00:00', tz='UTC')

db_path <- 'data/Sample.db'

# Create the class and load the data
pp = Postprocessing()
pp$load_data(start_dt, end_dt, db=db_path)
## Joining, by = "id_name"
glimpse(pp$data)

Data filtering

At the moment filtering is only done using Eddy Pro quality flags (QC flag == 1) and then outlier exclusion using simple quantile methods.

pp$filter_co2()
pp$filter_ch4()

Partition flux

pp$flux_partitioning(plot=TRUE)

Contribution class

This class uses the Kljun et al.(2015) model to calculate the flux footprint.

Methods are available to calculate the percent contribution within area of interest and to return a timeseries raster brick.

source('src/postprocessing.R')
cb = Contribution(data = pp$data,
                  xy = c(117467, 461350),
                  epsg = 28992,
                  shapefile = 'data/geodata/zegveld_perceel.gpkg')
# The number of cores to use can be specified with parallel
cb$calculate_contribution(parallel=4)
## Calculating footprints
## 49.559 sec elapsed
## Warning in showSRID(uprojargs, format = "PROJ", multiline = "NO", prefer_proj
## = prefer_proj): Discarded datum Unknown based on Bessel 1841 ellipsoid in Proj4
## definition
## Calculating contribution percentage
## 23.81 sec elapsed

Plot of contribution vs flux

pp$data %>% 
  mutate(Contribution = cb$cdata$Contribution) %>% 
  select(Contribution, FCH4, FC) %>% 
  pivot_longer(-Contribution) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(Contribution, value)) +
  geom_point() +
  facet_wrap(~name, scales='free_y')

Contribution timeseries

Calling calculate_contribution also stores a raster brick with the contribution timesteps, however it can also be run using:

cb$calculate_footprints()
# With parallel processing
cb$calculate_footprints(parallel=4)

Plot a timestep

rasterVis::gplot(cb$footprints[[1]]) +
  geom_raster(aes(fill=value)) +
  scale_fill_gradientn(colours = terrain.colors(7, rev=TRUE)) +
  scale_y_continuous(expand = c(0,0)) +
  scale_x_continuous(expand = c(0,0)) +
  ggtitle(names(cb$footprints[[1]]))

Upload to database

Updates the database with some of the variables calculated e.g., NEE, GPP, gap-filled series, contribution.

pp$data <- pp$data %>% 
  mutate(Contribution = cb$cdata$Contribution)

pp$upload_data(db=db_path)
